      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "High-density zoning can indeed lead to gentrification, as it often attracts wealthier residents and businesses, displacing long-time residents who can't afford the rising costs of living. This displacement disproportionately affects low-income and minority communities, who are often already struggling to make ends meet. However, proponents of high-density zoning argue that inclusive zoning policies, such as rent control and community land trusts, can help mitigate this effect and ensure that the benefits of urban development are shared equitably among all residents.",
