    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean \"mitigating\" sounds like a way to avoid the main problem though. if the whole point of high density is to make cities \"vibrant\" and \"inclusive\" for everyone, why does it seem like we always end up just building luxury condos for rich people? doesn't that make the whole idea kind of a failure in practice?",
